<title type="html"><![CDATA[Auto-strip quote when it's of entire previous message?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6483&amp;p=62831#p62831"><![CDATA[
Let me explain in a manner that someone implementing this feature could understand:<br /><br />Before adding a post N to a topic, read the recent post R from the topic. If N begins with a [quote] element, let Q be the inner markup of this element. If Q = R, remove this [quote] element from N before writing it to the database. For more robustness, case-fold and remove whitespace from Q and R before comparing them.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Jun 11, 2010 5:29 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
